{"lemma":"تَعْرِيفاتٌ","slug":"تَعْرِيفاتٌ","root":"ع.ر.ف","root_slug":"ع-ر-ف","root_link":"/words/roots/ع-ر-ف","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":9},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n28726"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AA%D9%8E%D8%B9%D9%92%D8%B1%D9%90%D9%8A%D9%81%D8%A7%D8%AA%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of عَرَّفَ (ʕarrafa) (form II)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"definition","examples":[{"text":"وإنما قال المصنف «كلامنا» ليعلم أن التعريف إنما هو للكلام في اصطلاح النحويين، لا في اصطلاح اللغوين، وهو في اللغة: اسم لكل ما يُتَكَلَّمُ به، مفيدًا كان أو غير مفيد."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"announcement"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"instruction"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"introduction"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"description"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"tariff"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"assertion"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"guessing"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Verbal noun of عَرَّفَ (ʕarrafa)."},"ipa":["/taʕ.riːf/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n28726","headword_ar":"تَعْرِيفٌ","root":"Erf","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"signifies The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"making to know;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iEolaAmN","text_ar":"اـِعْلَامٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, O, K, TA:) [or rather it has a more restricted signification than the latter word, as is indicated in the preceding paragraph:] and in this sense its verb may have two objective complements: one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Er~fhu AlA^amora","text_ar":"عرّفهُ الاَمْرَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made him to know the affair,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"case;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEolamahu A_iy~aAhu","text_ar":"اَعْلَمَهُ اـِيَّاهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": [or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he acquainted him with it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"told him of it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Er~fhu bayotahu","text_ar":"عرّفهُ بَيْتَهُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made him to know,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"acquainted him with, the place of his house,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tent;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEolamahu bimakaAnihi","text_ar":"اَعْلَمَهُ بِمَكَانِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) [and] one says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ear~afotuhu bihi","text_ar":"عَرَّفْتُهُ بِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I made him to know it by means of any of the five senses"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by mental perception;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ear~afotuhu A_iy~aAhu","text_ar":"عَرَّفْتُهُ اـِيَّاهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Msb.) See also 1, former half. And see 4. ―         -b2-  Also The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"making known; contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tanokiyrN","text_ar":"تَنْكِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (O, K.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ear~afa baEoDahu","text_ar":"عَرَّفَ بَعْضَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the Kur [lxvi. 3], has been expl. as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made known part thereof."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA. [For other explanations, see 1.]) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ear~afotuhu bizayodK","text_ar":"عَرَّفْتُهُ بِزَيْدٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I made him known by the name of Zeyd;"},{"kind":"text","text":"like the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sam~ayotuhu bizayodK","text_ar":"سَمَّيْتُهُ بِزَيْدٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Sb, TA.) ―         -b3-  [Hence, The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"explaining"},{"kind":"text","text":"a term: and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an explanation"},{"kind":"text","text":"thereof: thus used, its pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taEoriyfaAtN","text_ar":"تَعْرِيفَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": it has a less restricted meaning than"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Had~N","text_ar":"حَدٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which signifies the “ defining, ” and “ a definition. ” ―         -b4-  And The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"making"},{"kind":"text","text":"a noun, or a nominal proposition,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"determinate."},{"kind":"text","text":"―         -b5-  Hence also,] The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"crying"},{"kind":"text","text":"a stray-beast, or a beast or some other thing that has been lost; (S, TA;) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mentioning"},{"kind":"text","text":"it ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and describing"},{"kind":"text","text":"it]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and seeking to find him who had knowledge"},{"kind":"text","text":"of it. (TA.) ―         -b6-  And [hence likewise,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Er~fhu bi*anobihi","text_ar":"عرّفهُ بِذَنْبِهِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He branded him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stigmatized him, with his misdeed."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)       -A2-  Also The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rendering"},{"kind":"text","text":"[a thing]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fragrant;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, * K, * TA;) from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEarofu","text_ar":"العَرْفُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S:) and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"adorning"},{"kind":"text","text":"[it],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"decorating"},{"kind":"text","text":"[it], or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"embellishing"},{"kind":"text","text":"[it]. (TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ear~afahaA lahumo","text_ar":"عَرَّفَهَا لَهُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the Kur [xlvii. 7], is said to mean"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He hath rendered it fragrant"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e. Paradise ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aljan~ap","text_ar":"الجَنَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":")]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for them:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O:) or it means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He hath described it to them so that, when they enter it, they shall know it by that description,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or so"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that they shall know their places of abode therein:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He hath described it to them, and made them desirous of it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Er-Rághib, TA:) [and the like is said by Bd:] or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He hath defined it for them so that there shall be for every one a distinct paradise."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd.) ―         -b2-  One says also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Er~f raA^osahu biAld~uhoni","text_ar":"عرّف رَاْسَهُ بِالدُّهْنِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He moistened the hair of his head abundantly with oil,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with the oil;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raw~aAhu","text_ar":"رَوَّاهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Er~f TaEaAmahu","text_ar":"عرّف طَعَامَهُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made his food to have much seasoning,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"condiment."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)       -A3-  Also The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"halting"},{"kind":"text","text":"[of the pilgrims]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"at 'Arafát."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Er~fwA","text_ar":"عرّفوا"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Mgh, O, Msb,) inf. n. as above,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They halted at 'Arafát;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"they were present at 'Arafát;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O.) And [hence], in a postclassical sense,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They imitated the people of 'Arafát, in some other place, by going forth to the desert and there praying, and humbling themselves,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"offering earnest supplication;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by assembling in their mosques to pray and to beg forgiveness:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Har p. 672:) the first who did this was Ibn-'Abbás, at El-Basrah. (Mgh, and Har ubi suprá.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Er~f biAlhadoYi","text_ar":"عرّف بِالهَدْىِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He brought the animal for sacrifice to 'Arafát."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh.)       -A4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Er~f Al$~ar~a bayonahumo","text_ar":"عرّف الشَّرَّ بَيْنَهُمْ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He excited evil,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mischief, between them,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"among them:"},{"kind":"text","text":"the verb in this phrase being formed by permutation from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a ~a va","text_ar":"اَ َّ ثَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Yaakoob, TA.)"},{"kind":"page_break","n":2014}],"source_refs":["S","O","K","TA","Mgh","Msb"]}]}}